  "diagnostic_reasoning": "The symptom of hard starting when cold, but normal starting when warm, strongly indicates an issue with the cold-start enrichment system. On a 1965 Mustang with an Autolite 2100 2bbl carburetor, this points directly to the automatic choke. If the choke plate is not closing fully or the fast idle cam is not properly engaged, the engine will run lean during cold cranking, requiring extended cranking to fire. The FSM (Source 59) describes the function of the fast idle cam for cold engine operation.",
